The fluorescent probe SOSG and DPBF measured the generation of 1O2. ITIC-Th NPs (25 μg/mL, ddH2O) were mixed with SOSG solution and irradiated by a 660 nm laser (1.0 W/cm2) over 10 min. The fluorescence spectrum of oxidized SOSG (excitation/emission: 488/525 nm) was recorded by a UV vis NIR spectrophotometer every 10 s. ITIC-Th NPs (25 μg/mL, dichloromethane) and DPBF (2 μM) were dissolved into THF, then the solution was followed by irradiation (660 nm, 1.0 W/cm2), then immediately detected the UV–Vis absorption. The 1O2 quantum yield was evaluated by previous literature using Formula (2) [28].φ(unkown)=φΔrefk(unkown)k(ref)F(ref)F(unkown)PF(ref)PF(unkown)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
